3. A method for centering a workpiece on a metal shaping machine, comprising the steps of:
(a) providing first and second guide plates having respective first and second aligned bores therein for supporting a centering pin mounted therein for axial movement between a retracted position and a use position;
(b) engaging at least one spring with the centering pin for exerting a predetermined axial bias against the centering pin in the direction of the workpiece for urging the centering pin into the use position; and
(c) locking the centering pin in the use position during the operation of the machine on the workpiece;
(d) wherein the step of engaging at least one spring with the centering pin comprises the step of biasing a centrally-disposed beam of a triple beam spring against the centering pin in the direction of the workpiece for urging the centering pin into the use position.

7. A method for centering a workpiece on a metal shaping machine, comprising the steps of:
(a) providing first and second guide plates having respective first and second aligned bores therein for supporting a centering pin mounted therein for axial movement between a retracted position and a use position;
(b) engaging at least one spring with the centering pin for exerting a predetermined axial bias against the centering pin in the direction of the workpiece for urging the centering pin into the use position; and
(c) locking the centering pin in the use position during the operation of the machine on the workpiece;
(d) wherein the step of engaging at least one spring with the centering pin comprises the step of biasing a centrally-disposed beam of a triple beam spring against the centering pin in the direction of the workpiece for urging the centering pin into the use position.
